=A0<em>down</em>, as the market makers hedged both sold puts and bought cal=
ls by selling GameStop stock.[3] Retail traders YOLOing short-dated out-of-=
the-money call options does not seem to explain much of what happened in Ga=
meStop=E2=80=99s big week.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What else? Did G=
ameStop eventually crash late in that week because Robinhood limited its cu=
stomers=E2=80=99 ability to buy the stock? Maybe, why not, though the SEC d=
oesn=E2=80=99t really take a position. But did Robinhood impose limits beca=
use of some evil conspiracy with hedge funds and market makers? No, of cour=
se not; Robinhood (and other brokers) imposed limits on GameStop (and other=
 meme stock) trading because of margin requirements at their clearinghouses=
.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The way <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/25393723.275721/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDEtMjkvcmVkZGl0LXRyYWRlcnMtb24tcm9iaW5ob29kLW=
