=80=9CLet=E2=80=99s all buy GameStop and get rich=E2=80=9D was absolutely a=
 weird game-like positive feedback loop that led investors to trade more th=
an they would otherwise, but Robinhood=E2=80=99s app design had nothing to =
do with it.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So the SEC=E2=80=99s report doe=
sn=E2=80=99t so much explain=C2=A0what happened to GameStop; really it just=
=C2=A0<em>rules out=C2=A0</em>various popular, technical-ish, conspiracy-is=
h explanations. =E2=80=9CYou see, GameStop=E2=80=99s stock went up 2,700% i=
n January[8] on no news because of this complex equation involving gamma, r=
etail options volume, short positioning and sunspots=E2=80=9D is a good exp=
lanation in that (1) it explains a weird thing in a weird way and (2)=C2=A0=
reading it makes you feel smart and in-the-know. But, the SEC says =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0and I think they=E2=80=99re probably right =E2=80=94=C2=A0it isn=
=E2=80=99t true.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CYou see, GameStop=
=E2=80=99s stock went up 2,700% in January on no news because a bunch of sm=
all retail investors simultaneously decided to buy it=E2=80=9D is a bad exp=
lanation in that it explains a wild phenomenon in a boring way, and in that=
 it doesn=E2=80=99t tell you anything=C2=A0useful. There is no technical fi=
x to market structure that would prevent that sort of thing from happening,=
 nor is it obvious that you=E2=80=99d want to prevent <em>that</em> sort of=
 thing (people all deciding to buy a stock) from happening. There is=C2=A0n=
o obvious set of technical indicators that would help you identify future w=
hatever-this-is situations;=C2=A0options positioning and short interest and=
 whatever seem to have been less important than just everyone in the world =
liking the stock at the same time.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On=
e other thing that might be worth mentioning is that the volume-weighted av=
erage price of GameStop stock during its crazy last week of January=C2=A0wa=
s $166.23.[9] It closed yesterday at $186.02. If you bought GameStop during=
 its insane week, you=E2=80=99re probably <em>up</em>. If your explanation =
of GameStop is =E2=80=9Cweird technical stuff happened that week and the pr=
ice went crazy,=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cevil conspiracies happened that week a=
nd the price went crazy,=E2=80=9D or even just =E2=80=9Cwe all collectively=
 lost our minds that week and the price went crazy,=E2=80=9D how do you exp=
