om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Green vs. anti-green</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The way it works is that there are com=
panies and each company does a range of projects. Some companies =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0particularly energy companies =E2=80=94=C2=A0will do all three of the=
se sorts of projects:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-lef=
t: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Green projec=
ts, where the company does something that is good for the environment. (Bui=
lding a wind farm, say.)</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Dirty pro=
jects, where the company does something that is bad for the environment but=
 nonetheless has positive expected value for the company. (Drilling for oil=
 in an arctic wildlife reserve, say.)</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5p=
x;">Neutral and miscellaneous projects, where the company does something th=
at doesn=E2=80=99t feel especially related to the environment one way or th=
e other. (Stock buybacks, I dunno.)</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">T=
he company needs money to fund these projects. Crudely, there are two ways =
to raise money: You can raise money specifically earmarked for a particular=
=C2=A0project, or you just raise money for general corporate purposes and u=
se the money for whichever projects you want. Crudely, you should choose a =
financing method based on what investors want: If there is a ton of=C2=A0in=
vestor demand for green projects, you should finance the green projects wit=
h specifically earmarked money; if there is a ton of investor resistance to=
 dirty projects, you should finance the dirty projects out of general corpo=
rate funds.[10]</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have <a href=3D"https://=
link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25393723.275721/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb=
21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTktMTItMDYvZ3JlZW4tYm9uZHMtd2l0aG91=
dC10aGUtYm9uZHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAxOTIxX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ=
1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjExMDE5JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leX=
N0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1a37cad6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">talked</a> a few times a=
bout =E2=80=9Cgreen bonds,=E2=80=9D which are bonds that a company (or coun=
try, etc.) issues specifically to finance green projects. Green bonds exist=
 because investors like to finance green projects, so green bonds tend to h=
ave a slightly lower interest rate than regular bonds of the same company: =
The company does whatever mix of projects it does, but investors prefer to =
explicitly finance the green ones. But we <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/25393723.275721/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAtMTQvaXQtcGF5cy10by1ub3QtcGF5LXlvdXItZGVidH=
M_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAxOTIxX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlP=
W5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjExMDE5JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB7d883e92" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">talked last week</a> about reports that=
 that is changing, as investors say, well, look, we want companies to be gr=
een in their overall mix of projects, but we don=E2=80=99t really get any g=
reat benefit out of specifically financing the green projects. If a company=
 mostly goes around polluting but also does one small solar project, we=E2=
=80=99re not gonna be all that jazzed to buy green bonds to finance the sol=
ar project. As the Financial Times <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/25393723.275721/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW=
9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAtMTQvaXQtcGF5cy10by1ub3QtcGF5LXlvdXItZGVidHM_Y21wa=
