ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">the Wall Street Journal</a> reporting that =E2=80=
=9CSome Investors Say Bank Pledges to Cut Funding for Arctic Drilling Conta=
in Loopholes=E2=80=9D:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Some of =
the world=E2=80=99s largest banks, including Goldman Sachs Group Inc., HSBC=
 Holdings=C2=A0PLC and BNP Paribas SA pledged in recent years to stop direc=
t financing of Arctic oil exploration. The idea was to choke off money for =
fossil-fuel extraction in a pristine natural environment.</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">A battle has broken out among investors, environmentalists a=
nd banks over those pledges. Some investors and environmentalists say they =
contain loopholes, and money has continued to flow from big banks to compan=
ies active in areas of Norway, Russia, Canada and Alaska rich in oil and ga=
s. Under pressure, two of the banks, BNP and HSBC, say they are reviewing t=
heir pledges to make them stronger. ...</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Amo=
ng the complaints about the pledges: While banks have stopped directly lend=
ing to Arctic projects through what are known as project finance loans, the=
y continue to lend to oil-and-gas companies active in the Arctic at the cor=
porate level, where money is fungible. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
x 0;">There is no indication that the banks have violated their promises, w=
hich focus on project finance, or lending to specific projects. But about 9=
0% of energy investments are financed primarily from company balance sheets=
, according to the International Energy Agency.</p></blockquote><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">Yes, right, if you go to the market and say =E2=80=9Cwe w=
ant to borrow money for green things,=E2=80=9D you might save a basis point=
, though you might not; now people just kind of expect you to do green thin=
gs. If you go to the market and say =E2=80=9Cwe want to borrow money for di=
rty things,=E2=80=9D you will miss out on some investors. =E2=80=9CCome on,=
=E2=80=9D those investors will say, =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=80=99re not going to giv=
e you money=C2=A0<em>specifically for the dirty things</em>, that looks ter=
rible.=E2=80=9D But if you go to the market and say =E2=80=9Cwe want to bor=
row money for all the things we use money for,=E2=80=9D some of them will b=
e clean and some of them will be dirty and it=E2=80=99s all basically fine.=
